programme.title: Paranormal State: Beer, Wine and Spirits

programme.title: Paranormal State: If I Should Die...

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dark Man

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vegas

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Fire
programme.desc: Christina has been experiencing paranormal activity ever since her father and step-mother were murdered near Columbus, OH last year. PRS and psychic/medium?Chip Coffey delve into a open murder case and wind up exposing a family divide.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Good Vs. Evil
programme.desc: PRS visits a western Pennsylvania couple wracked by a torrent of paranormal activity.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Family Ties

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kasteel Doorwerth, Arnhem, Netherlands

programme.title: Most Haunted: Kasteel Ammersoyen, Ammerzoden, Netherlands

programme.title: Most Haunted: Pleasley Vale Mills, Nottinghamshire
programme.desc: The team visits the remote Pleasley Vale Mills. With so many victims from its industrial past, who will choose to show their displeasure as the crew roam the mill's eerie and empty corridors?

programme.desc: Among the art and antiquities of Bodelwyddan Castle, the team discovers that some residents would rather not leave. They are prepared for a warm Welsh welcome, not a series of spine-chilling events.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love and Marriage - Part 1

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Love and Marriage - Part 2

programme.sub-title: Breaking Ground On A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Runaway Ready

programme.title: 10 Years Younger New Zealand: Kim Edgecombe
programme.desc: Fiona McDonald and the "10 Years" team of experts gear up for their toughest challenge yet! Kim Edgecombe is living proof that smoking really does cause premature aging. Kim needs help, but are the team too late?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Heather Williams Re-Visit

programme.desc: Marci is a former pageant girl, but kids, stress and lack of attention to her looks have sent her appearance south. With the help of a rare triple dose of doctor treatments and a Glam Squad overhaul, Marci hopes to remove the years of neglect.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Salto Mortale

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Remote Control

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Graduate

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Very First Time

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Highfall

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Behind the Scenes

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.sub-title: Return of the Dead: Glove II

programme.desc: Washington State, a hotbed of unexplained paranormal activity. Between possible UFOs in the sky and winged creatures in the woods, Ryan and his team are forced to face their fears and deal with the question: Are we truly alone in the universe?

programme.title: Paranormal State: Vendetta
programme.desc: P.R.S. investigates claims of supernatural revenge in the Pennsylvania Poconos. When a client's new boyfriend moves in, does the paranormal move in with him? Or did her ex put a hex on her house and the entire family?

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Ladder

programme.title: Paranormal State: The Devil in Syracuse
programme.desc: The clients are new, but the spirit is all too familiar as Ryan Buell prepares himself to battle the taunting demon that has been following him.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Dead Legends
programme.desc: PRS and Psychic/Medium Chip Coffey investigate the famed Hotel Conneaut in northern Pennsylvania. Heavy doors opening on their own, sightings of a boy, a bride and a menacing butcher have the hotel's staff on edge.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Shadow Caster
programme.desc: PRS investigates an Alabama home where clients, Georgiana and her two daughters, are so terrified, they moved out after only 18 months. They have seen shadow figures, been touched and have a recorded EVP stating, "Look at me, get out of here."

programme.title: Paranormal State: Satan's Soldier
programme.desc: Mark and Kim can't sleep through the racket caused by unseen forces in their central Indiana home. When PRS and Psychic/Medium Michelle Belanger discover what appears to be blood in the basement, they investigate a history of violence in the home.

programme.title: Paranormal State: Woman in the Window
programme.desc: Ryan and his team lend paranormal assistance to a family who lives in a historic home that was once a part of the Underground Railroad. Does the answer to their haunting lie in the mysterious tunnels beneath the house?

programme.desc: Among the art and antiquities of Bodelwyddan Castle, the team discovers that some residents would rather not leave. They are prepared for a warm Welsh welcome, not a series of spine-chilling events.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Annesley Hall, Nottinghamshire
programme.desc: From style and splendor to danger and desolation, the team is horrified by the sinister secrets that Annesley Hall still harbors. Their investigation culminates in an amazing phenomenon.

programme.title: Most Haunted: Lower Southwood Cottage

programme.title: Most Haunted: Castle Keep
programme.desc: One of the oldest sites the team has visited, Castle Keep was once a county jail with a number of tormented souls. Many have seen dark shadows, as well as a white light, in the gallery.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song of Songs
programme.desc: A struggling pianist tries to start life again after a heart attack.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Night to Remember
programme.desc: High school seniors hope they get the dates they want for prom.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Mother and a Daughter

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in the Limelight

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: 24-Hour Makeover

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Picture Perfect

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Payback
programme.desc: A mysterious death by poisoning creates questions about the safety of portal technology. When a Taelon is killed in the same manner, the investigation leads to a very smart scientist that even the Resistance was scared to work with.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Friendly Fire
programme.desc: Paul Chandler plots an attack on the Taelon Embassy in DC with the ship he stole from Lili. He begs her to join him in beginning an all out war.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Volunteers
programme.desc: A group of Resistance capture a volunteer from a Taelon program for youth. Liam decides they may learn valuable information from her. They also decide to send in one of their own as a volunteer to see what the program is teaching.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Bliss
programme.desc: Lili is given a psychotropic drug called "bliss" via a Taelon device. They discover it is widespread. With an instantly strong addictive property, the addicts are dying within 48 hours. The investigation leads Liam and Sandoval to Ireland.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Highjacked
programme.desc: With a reporter on board, the Taelon mother ship is highjacked into interdimensional space. Liam is the prime suspect, causing an even bigger rift between Da'an and Zo'or. As the ship floats, lost in space, they must find the real culprit.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Defector
programme.desc: A shuttle crashes on a beach after being pursued by a second Taelon piloted shuttle. When Liam locates the survivor (a Taelon called Belleye), he claims to want to help the Resistance take back Earth from the Taelons.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak
programme.desc: Augur is recruited by a Taelon weapons project, but the others are worried about his involvement. When the project is launched earlier than originally planned to fight a Jiridian fleet, the Earth is in danger.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle
programme.desc: A Jiridian probe headed for Earth is shot down by the Taelon Embassy and crashes outside of D.C. Liam recovers the probe, but he, Augur, and Julia are captured by another underground resistance movement led by the real Colonel Liam Kincaid.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Crossfire
programme.desc: As the election draws near, Liam believes Zo'or is trying to have Jonathan Doors murdered. The Resistance worries that an attack is imminent at the final debate. Julia mobilizes a group to protect Doors against Liam's wishes.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Poker Face

programme.title: Homicide Hunter

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Lockdown
programme.desc: When a crazed gunman terrorizes his neighborhood, officers put themselves in the line of fire to restore order.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Inside Puppy Mills

programme.desc: Pug and pet pig get rowdy; emotionally scarred Shepherd; two Dachshunds make an unsavory mix.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Power of the Pack

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Dasher, Riley, and Fosse

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Dark Side of Chipper
programme.desc: Chipper, a 2-month old Ridgeback/Boxer mix has become progressively more aggressive and has attacked 5 dogs. Two Whippets, Rudy and Monte, are causing issues at their owner’s place of business.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Tori, Cassie & Skyler, and Tallulah, Bella, Boris, & Groucho, and Howie

programme.sub-title: Tori, Cassie & Skyler, and Tallulah, Bella, Boris, & Groucho, and Howie

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Language of Scrout
programme.desc: A Doberman Mix has taken control of his family home; an animal communicator calls for back-up with her Doberman Pinscher; and a comedienne enlists Cesar's help for her two temperamental rescue dogs.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Ventriloquist/Cat Lady
programme.desc: April's addiction to her puppets has gotten so strong she can't go anywhere without them. Debbie is severely allergic to cats, but has over twenty of them, leaving her in isolation.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Can’t Stop Cleaning/Love Rocks
programme.desc: Cyntrelle dropped out of high school because of her addiction to cleaning. Belinda's obsession with rocks has taken over her life, with more than 100,000 scattered around her home.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: East Glass/Bleaches Skin
programme.desc: Josh has eaten more than 250 light bulbs. But is he really addicted to the attention that he receives? Candice thinks dark skin is ugly and has resorted to using dangerous bleaching creams.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Make-up Addict/Obsessed with Death
programme.desc: Maureen won't go out of the house without a full face of makeup. Meanwhile, Barbara is so obsessed with death that she's planned her own funeral.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Laxatives and Pottery/Ashes
programme.desc: Kimberly takes hundreds of laxatives a day in an attempt to lose weight. Meanwhile, Bianca prefers to eat pottery and cigarette ashes instead of food.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Wears Diapers/Eats Dryer Sheets
programme.desc: For Riley, there's nothing like the comfort of wearing a warm, wet diaper. She lives as an adult baby to escape the stresses of life. And Charmissa chews on dryer sheets for up to 10 hours a day.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Rampant Rats/Extreme Fingernails
programme.desc: Theresa has more than 60 pet hairless rats that are taking over her apartment. Jazz has been growing her fingernails for 22 years. Her longest nail is two feet long, and she calls them her children.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Drinks Nail Polish & Ear Digger

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Vapor Rubs/Eats Tires

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: The Lamb/Eats Deodorant

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Pony Play / Addicted to Drinking Paint
